  "question": "Logistic Regression",
  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n<title>Interactive Logistic Regression Demo</title>\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n<style>\n  body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial; margin: 16px; color: #222; }\n  h1 { margin: 6px 0 8px 0; font-size: 20px; }\n  p { margin: 6px 0; }\n  #container { display: flex; gap: 18px; align-items: flex-start; }\n  #left { width: 620px; }\n  canvas { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #ddd; display: block; }\n  #controls { margin-top: 10px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 8px; }\n  label { display: block; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 4px; }\n  .row { display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; }\n  .btn { padding: 8px 10px; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid #bbb; background: #f6f6f6; cursor: pointer; }\n  .btn.primary { background: #2b8aef; color: white; border-color: #1670d8; }\n  .btn.warn { background: #ffefef; border-color: #ffbcbc; }\n  .small { font-size: 13px; padding: 6px 8px; }\n  input[type=\"range\"] { width: 100%; }\n  .info { font-size: 13px; background:#fcfcfc; padding:8px; border-radius:6px; border: 1px solid #eee; }\n  #right { flex: 1; min-width: 320px; }\n  .stat { font-size: 14px; margin: 6px 0; }\n  .code { background:#111; color:#0f0; padding:8px; border-radius:6px; font-family: monospace; font-size:13px; white-space:pre-wrap; }\n  footer { margin-top: 14px; font-size: 12px; color:#666;}\n  .controls-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap:8px; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Interactive Logistic Regression Demo</h1>\n<p>This interactive demo shows binary logistic regression on 2D points. Click to add points, generate datasets, and train a logistic model (weights updated by gradient descent). The background shows predicted probability (blue = class 1, red = class 0). The decision boundary is drawn where p = 0.5.</p>\n\n<div id=\"container\">\n  <div id=\"left\">\n    <canvas id=\"plot\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\"></canvas>\n    <div id=\"controls\" style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n      <div>\n        <label>Mode: add points as class</label>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n          <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"addClass\" value=\"1\" checked /> Class 1 (blue)</label>\n          <label><input type=\"radio\" name=\"addClass\" value=\"0\" /> Class 0 (red)</label>\n        </div>\n        <div style=\"margin-top:8px\" class=\"row\">\n          <button class=\"btn small\" id=\"clear\">Clear points</button>\n          <button class=\"btn small\" id=\"generate-sep\">Generate separable</button>\n          <button class=\"btn small\" id=\"generate-mixed\">Generate mixed</button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div>\n        <label>Training controls</label>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n          <button class=\"btn primary small\" id=\"run\">Run</button>\n          <button class=\"btn small\" id=\"pause\" disabled>Pause</button>\n          <button class=\"btn small\" id=\"step\">Step</button>\n          <button class=\"btn small\" id=\"reset-weights\">Reset weights</button>\n        </div>\n        <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n          <label>Learning rate: <span id=\"lrVal\">0.5</span></label>\n          <input type=\"range\" id=\"lr\" min=\"0.001\" max=\"2\" step=\"0.001\" value=\"0.5\" />\n        </div>\n        <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n          <label>Regularization λ (L2): <span id=\"regVal\">0.0</span></label>\n          <input type=\"range\" id=\"reg\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.001\" value=\"0\" />\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div>\n        <label>Data</label>\n        <div class=\"row\">\n          <label>Points: <span id=\"nPoints\">0</span></label>\n          <label>Accuracy: <span id=\"acc\">-</span></label>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-top:6px;\">\n          <label>Epochs run: <span id=\"epochs\">0</span></label>\n          <label>Loss: <span id=\"loss\">-</span></label>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div>\n        <label>Model</label>\n        <div class=\"info\">\n          <div class=\"stat\">Weights: <span id=\"wVal\">[0, 0]</span></div>\n          <div class=\"stat\">Bias: <span id=\"bVal\">0</span></div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n      <label>Loss curve</label>\n      <canvas id=\"lossChart\" width=\"600\" height=\"140\"></canvas>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"right\">\n    <h3>How it works</h3>\n    <p>\n      Logistic regression models the probability that a point (x,y) belongs to class 1:\n    </p>\n    <div class=\"info\">\n      p = σ(w1*x + w2*y + b), where σ(z) = 1 / (1 + e^-z)\n    </div>\n    <p>\n      We minimize the average cross-entropy loss:\n    </p>\n    <div class=\"info\">\n      L = -1/N Σ[y log p + (1-y) log(1-p)] + (λ/2) * ||w||^2\n    </div>\n    <p>Gradient descent updates the weights w, b using the average gradient (p - y) times inputs. Use the controls to change the learning rate and regularization. Click the canvas to add points (choose class above).</p>\n\n    <h3>Tips</h3>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Generate \"separable\" to see near-perfect classification.</li>\n      <li>Increase learning rate to speed training; too large may diverge.</li>\n      <li>Regularization helps when data overlaps (prevents large weights).</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <h3>Implementation notes</h3>\n    <div class=\"code\" id=\"impl\">\n      Logistic regression implemented with full-batch gradient descent.\n      Canvas used to draw probability heatmap (background), points, and decision boundary (p=0.5).\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<footer>Left-click on the plot to add points. Choose which class to add using the radio buttons. Right-click is disabled for adding.</footer>\n\n<script>\n/*\nInteractive Logistic Regression Demo\n- 2D inputs scaled to [-1,1] range for both axes.\n- Full-batch gradient descent updating weights (w1,w2) and bias b.\n- Background shows predicted probability; decision boundary drawn where p=0.5.\n- Click to add points: select class (0 or 1) using radios.\n*/\n\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('plot');\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d', { alpha: false });\nconst lossCanvas = document.getElementById('lossChart');\nconst lctx = lossCanvas.getContext('2d');\n\nlet points = []; // {x: in canvas coords, y:, fx: feature x in [-1,1], fy:, label:0/1}\nconst W = { w1: randomRange(-1,1), w2: randomRange(-1,1), b: randomRange(-0.5,0.5) };\nlet running = false;\nlet epoch = 0;\nlet losses = [];\n\nconst lrSlider = document.getElementById('lr');\nconst lrVal = document.getElementById('lrVal');\nconst regSlider = document.getElementById('reg');\nconst regVal = document.getElementById('regVal');\nconst nPointsEl = document.getElementById('nPoints');\nconst accEl = document.getElementById('acc');\nconst epochsEl = document.getElementById('epochs');\nconst lossEl = document.getElementById('loss');\nconst wValEl = document.getElementById('wVal');\nconst bValEl = document.getElementById('bVal');\n\nlrSlider.addEventListener('input', ()=> lrVal.textContent = Number(lrSlider.value).toFixed(3));\nregSlider.addEventListener('input', ()=> regVal.textContent = Number(regSlider.value).toFixed(3));\n\ndocument.getElementById('clear').addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n  points = [];\n  epoch = 0; losses = [];\n  updateStats(); draw();\n});\ndocument.getElementById('generate-sep').addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n  generateDataset(true);\n});\ndocument.getElementById('generate-mixed').addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n  generateDataset(false);\n});\ndocument.getElementById('run').addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n  running = true; document.getElementById('run').disabled = true;\n  document.getElementById('pause').disabled = false;\n  animate();\n});\ndocument.getElementById('pause').addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n  running = false; document.getElementById('run').disabled = false;\n  document.getElementById('pause').disabled = true;\n});\ndocument.getElementById('step').addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n  step();\n});\ndocument.getElementById('reset-weights').addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n  W.w1 = randomRange(-1,1); W.w2 = randomRange(-1,1); W.b = randomRange(-0.5,0.5);\n  epoch = 0; losses = [];\n  updateStats(); draw();\n});\n\n// canvas click to add points\nconst addClassRadios = document.getElementsByName('addClass');\nlet addClass = 1;\nfor(const r of addClassRadios) r.addEventListener('change', ()=> { if(r.checked) addClass = Number(r.value); });\ncanvas.addEventListener('mousedown', (ev)=>{\n  ev.preventDefault();\n  const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();\n  const cx = ev.clientX - rect.left;\n  const cy = ev.clientY - rect.top;\n  addPointFromCanvas(cx, cy, addClass);\n});\ncanvas.addEventListener('contextmenu', (ev)=>{ ev.preventDefault(); }); // block menu\n\n// helpers\nfunction randomRange(a,b){ return a + Math.random()*(b-a); }\nfunction addPointFromCanvas(cx, cy, label){\n  const fx = (cx / canvas.width) * 2 - 1;\n  const fy = -((cy / canvas.height) * 2 - 1); // invert y so top is +1\n  points.push({cx, cy, fx, fy, label});\n  epoch = 0; losses = [];\n  updateStats(); draw();\n}\n\nfunction generateDataset(linear=true){\n  points = [];\n  const n = 80;\n  if(linear){\n    // create roughly separable clusters by a random line\n    const angle = randomRange(-Math.PI/2, Math.PI/2);\n    const nx = Math.cos(angle), ny = Math.sin(angle);\n    const offset = randomRange(-0.2, 0.2);\n    for(let i=0;i<n;i++){\n      let fx = randomRange(-1,1), fy = randomRange(-1,1);\n      const s = nx*fx + ny*fy + offset;\n      const label = s>0 ? 1 : 0;\n      const cx = (fx+1)/2 * canvas.width;\n      const cy = (1 - (fy+1)/2) * canvas.height;\n      points.push({cx, cy, fx, fy, label});\n    }\n  }else{\n    // mixed clusters (non-linearly separable)\n    for(let i=0;i<n;i++){\n      let r = randomRange(0, 0.9);\n      let theta = randomRange(0, Math.PI*2);\n      // two overlapping blobs\n      let cxOffset = i%2===0 ? 0.4 : -0.4;\n      let fx = cxOffset + 0.4 * Math.cos(theta) * r + randomRange(-0.05,0.05);\n      let fy = 0.4 * Math.sin(theta) * r + randomRange(-0.05,0.05);\n      fx = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, fx));\n      fy = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, fy));\n      let label = i%2===0 ? 1 : 0;\n      const cx = (fx+1)/2 * canvas.width;\n      const cy = (1 - (fy+1)/2) * canvas.height;\n      points.push({cx, cy, fx, fy, label});\n    }\n  }\n  epoch = 0; losses = [];\n  updateStats(); draw();\n}\n\n// compute model prediction p in [0,1] given features\nfunction predictProb(fx, fy){\n  // z = w1*fx + w2*fy + b\n  const z = W.w1*fx + W.w2*fy + W.b;\n  // stable sigmoid\n  if(z >= 0) {\n    const ez = Math.exp(-z);\n    return 1 / (1 + ez);\n  } else {\n    const ez = Math.exp(z);\n    return ez / (1 + ez);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction computeLossAndGrad(){\n  if(points.length === 0) return {loss:0, gw1:0, gw2:0, gb:0};\n  let loss = 0;\n  let gw1 = 0, gw2 = 0, gb = 0;\n  const N = points.length;\n  const lambda = Number(regSlider.value);\n  for(const p of points){\n    const z = W.w1*p.fx + W.w2*p.fy + W.b;\n    // compute p (sigmoid) with numerical care\n    let pred;\n    if(z >= 0){\n      const ez = Math.exp(-z);\n      pred = 1/(1+ez);\n    } else {\n      const ez = Math.exp(z);\n      pred = ez/(1+ez);\n    }\n    // clamp probabilities away from 0/1 for loss stability\n    const eps = 1e-12;\n    const pp = Math.min(1-eps, Math.max(eps, pred));\n    loss += -(p.label * Math.log(pp) + (1-p.label) * Math.log(1-pp));\n    const diff = pred - p.label; // gradient factor\n    gw1 += diff * p.fx;\n    gw2 += diff * p.fy;\n    gb += diff;\n  }\n  // average\n  loss /= N;\n  gw1 /= N; gw2 /= N; gb /= N;\n  // L2 regularization on weights (not bias)\n  loss += (lambda/2) * (W.w1*W.w1 + W.w2*W.w2);\n  gw1 += lambda * W.w1;\n  gw2 += lambda * W.w2;\n  return {loss, gw1, gw2, gb};\n}\n\nfunction step(){\n  if(points.length === 0) return;\n  const lr = Number(lrSlider.value);\n  const {loss, gw1, gw2, gb} = computeLossAndGrad();\n  // gradient descent update\n  W.w1 -= lr * gw1;\n  W.w2 -= lr * gw2;\n  W.b  -= lr * gb;\n  epoch += 1;\n  losses.push(loss);\n  updateStats();\n  draw();\n}\n\n// compute current accuracy\nfunction computeAccuracy(){\n  if(points.length===0) return 0;\n  let correct = 0;\n  for(const p of points){\n    const prob = predictProb(p.fx, p.fy);\n    const predLabel = prob >= 0.5 ? 1 : 0;\n    if(predLabel === p.label) correct++;\n  }\n  return correct / points.length;\n}\n\nfunction updateStats(){\n  nPointsEl.textContent = points.length;\n  accEl.textContent = points.length>0 ? (100*computeAccuracy()).toFixed(1)+\"%\" : \"-\";\n  epochsEl.textContent = epoch;\n  lossEl.textContent = losses.length? losses[losses.length-1].toFixed(4) : \"-\";\n  wValEl.textContent = \"[\"+W.w1.toFixed(3)+\", \"+W.w2.toFixed(3)+\"]\";\n  bValEl.textContent = W.b.toFixed(3);\n  drawLoss();\n}\n\n// draw probability heatmap background, points, decision boundary\nfunction draw(){\n  // clear white background\n  ctx.fillStyle = '#ffffff';\n  ctx.fillRect(0,0,canvas.width,canvas.height);\n\n  // draw probability heatmap (sample at a grid)\n  const step = 6; // px step for speed\n  for(let px=0; px<canvas.width; px+=step){\n    for(let py=0; py<canvas.height; py+=step){\n      const fx = (px / canvas.width) * 2 - 1;\n      const fy = -((py / canvas.height) * 2 - 1);\n      const p = predictProb(fx, fy);\n      // color from red (0) to blue (1)\n      const r = Math.round(220*(1-p) + 240*(1-p)*0.1); // slightly brighten\n      const g = Math.round(220*(1-p) + 240*p*0.0);\n      const b = Math.round(220*p + 240*p*0.1 + 10*(1-p));\n      ctx.fillStyle = `rgb(${r},${g},${b})`;\n      ctx.fillRect(px, py, step, step);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // draw decision boundary where z = 0 (p=0.5)\n  // Solve for y: w2*y = -(w1*x + b) => y = -(w1*x + b)/w2\n  ctx.lineWidth = 2;\n  ctx.strokeStyle = '#222';\n  ctx.beginPath();\n  if(Math.abs(W.w2) > 1e-6){\n    // sample two x extremes in feature coords and map to canvas coords\n    const x1 = -1, x2 = 1;\n    const y1 = -(W.w1*x1 + W.b) / W.w2;\n    const y2 = -(W.w1*x2 + W.b) / W.w2;\n    const cx1 = (x1 + 1)/2 * canvas.width;\n    const cy1 = (1 - (y1 + 1)/2) * canvas.height;\n    const cx2 = (x2 + 1)/2 * canvas.width;\n    const cy2 = (1 - (y2 + 1)/2) * canvas.height;\n    ctx.moveTo(cx1, cy1);\n    ctx.lineTo(cx2, cy2);\n  } else {\n    // vertical-ish boundary: x = -b/w1\n    if(Math.abs(W.w1) > 1e-6){\n      const fx = -W.b / W.w1;\n      const cx = (fx + 1)/2 * canvas.width;\n      ctx.moveTo(cx, 0);\n      ctx.lineTo(cx, canvas.height);\n    }\n  }\n  ctx.stroke();\n\n  // draw axes ticks and origin marker (0,0)\n  ctx.fillStyle = '#333';\n  ctx.font = '12px sans-serif';\n  // x axis at y=0\n  const y0 = (1 - (0+1)/2) * canvas.height;\n  ctx.globalAlpha = 0.9;\n  ctx.beginPath(); ctx.strokeStyle = '#999'; ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n  ctx.moveTo(0, y0); ctx.lineTo(canvas.width, y0); ctx.stroke();\n  // y axis at x=0\n  const x0 = (0 + 1)/2 * canvas.width;\n  ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x0, 0); ctx.lineTo(x0, canvas.height); ctx.stroke();\n  ctx.globalAlpha = 1.0;\n\n  // draw points\n  for(const p of points){\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.arc(p.cx, p.cy, 6, 0, Math.PI*2);\n    ctx.fillStyle = p.label===1 ? '#1f77b4' : '#d9534f';\n    ctx.fill();\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;\n    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(255,255,255,0.85)';\n    ctx.stroke();\n  }\n\n  // overlay probability numbers on top-left\n  ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(0,0,0,0.6)';\n  ctx.font = '13px sans-serif';\n  ctx.fillText(`Points: ${points.length}`, 8, 16);\n  ctx.fillText(`Epoch: ${epoch}`, 8, 32);\n  if(losses.length) ctx.fillText(`Loss: ${losses[losses.length-1].toFixed(4)}`, 8, 48);\n}\n\nfunction drawLoss(){\n  // clear\n  lctx.fillStyle = '#fff'; lctx.fillRect(0,0,lossCanvas.width,lossCanvas.height);\n  lctx.strokeStyle = '#2b8aef'; lctx.lineWidth = 2;\n  const w = lossCanvas.width, h = lossCanvas.height;\n  if(losses.length === 0){\n    // axis\n    lctx.strokeStyle = '#ddd';\n    lctx.beginPath(); lctx.moveTo(0,h-20); lctx.lineTo(w,h-20); lctx.stroke();\n    return;\n  }\n  // find range\n  const maxL = Math.max(...losses);\n  const minL = Math.min(...losses);\n  const topPad = 10, bottomPad = 20;\n  lctx.beginPath();\n  for(let i=0;i<losses.length;i++){\n    const x = i/(losses.length-1) * (w-2) + 1;\n    const y = topPad + ( (losses[i]-minL) / Math.max(1e-9, (maxL-minL)) ) * (h-topPad-bottomPad);\n    const cy = h - (y + 0); // invert so higher loss at top\n    if(i===0) lctx.moveTo(x, cy); else lctx.lineTo(x, cy);\n  }\n  lctx.stroke();\n  // labels\n  lctx.fillStyle = '#444'; lctx.font = '12px sans-serif';\n  lctx.fillText('Loss', 6, 12);\n  lctx.fillText(minL.toFixed(3), 6, h-2);\n  lctx.fillText(maxL.toFixed(3), 6, 22);\n}\n\n// animation loop: run several steps per frame\nfunction animate(){\n  if(!running) return;\n  // do a small batch of steps per frame to speed up\n  const stepsPerFrame = 5;\n  for(let i=0;i<stepsPerFrame;i++){\n    step();\n  }\n  requestAnimationFrame(animate);\n}\n\n// initialize\n(function init(){\n  draw();\n  updateStats();\n})();\n\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
